@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - zpr/ZprPolicy
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired ZprPolicy spec, tracked status,\nand delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via GetZprPolicy;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListZprPolicies using filters compartment_id,\nname, id, lifecycle_state;
:Create the OCI resource via CreateZprPolicy\nwhen no reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteZprPolicy with required\nvia GetZprPolicy or ListZprPolicies to DELETED\nconfirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetZprPolicy or\nListZprPolicies until OCI reaches DELETED;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the imported\nfield surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartment_id, name;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateZprPolicy only for mutable fields\ndefined_tags, description, freeform_tags,\nstatements;
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: zpr
slug: zprpolicy
kind: ZprPolicy
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
supported drift: defined_tags, description,
freeform_tags, statements
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id, name
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_zpr_zpr_policies filters
compartment_id, name, id, lifecycle_state
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
ZprPolicy create, update, and delete are
work-request-backed through the ZPR service SDK.
The runtime projects the polled work request
into status.async.current as the canonical async
tracker and resumes in-flight OCI operations
from that shared status.
Create binds identity from an explicit OCI OCID
first and otherwise adopts only a unique
ListZprPolicies match on compartmentId plus
exact name before create; ambiguous matches fail
instead of guessing.
Mutable drift is limited to description,
statements, freeformTags, and definedTags.
compartmentId and name are replacement-only once
a live policy is bound.
Create, update, and delete recover or confirm
the tracked policy through GetZprPolicy and
GetZprPolicyWorkRequest. Delete completes only
after the work request reaches a terminal state
and GetZprPolicy confirms the policy is gone or
DELETED.
FAILED and NEEDS_ATTENTION remain terminal
non-success outcomes and do not collapse into
ACTIVE.
end note
@enduml
